WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:15.156 --> 00:00:16.498
- 'Morning.
- Hey.

2
00:00:16.518 --> 00:00:18.020
I'm just gonna go
look at flights.

3
00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:19.221
See when the next one leaves.

4
00:00:19.241 --> 00:00:20.783
I don't think I want to go.

5
00:00:20.803 --> 00:00:23.386
Your mother wouldn't have called
if it wasn't important.

6
00:00:24.768 --> 00:00:26.870
I just don't think
I can do this right now.

7
00:00:28.212 --> 00:00:30.354
He's your father. Cal.

8
00:00:30.374 --> 00:00:33.198
You don't know
what he can be like. Maggie.

9
00:00:33.218 --> 00:00:35.401
His schizophrenia
can get pretty bad.

10
00:00:35.421 --> 00:00:37.123
What if I came with you?

11
00:00:37.143 --> 00:00:39.525
You sure you want to do this?

12
00:00:39.545 --> 00:00:42.089
We're a team now. remember?

13
00:00:42.109 --> 00:00:44.692
Okay.

14
00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:10.763
Your pacing's just going to wear
a hole in the floor. Sully.

15
00:01:10.783 --> 00:01:13.446
What is taking Frank so long?

16
00:01:13.466 --> 00:01:15.889
The real estate office
only opened at 9:00.

17
00:01:15.909 --> 00:01:18.532
Well. somebody over there
has to know something.

18
00:01:18.552 --> 00:01:20.815
What did Maggie say?

19
00:01:20.835 --> 00:01:24.139
Didn't tell her.
She slept at Cal's last night.

20
00:01:24.159 --> 00:01:25.340
Really?

21
00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:29.025
Well. good morning.

22
00:01:29.045 --> 00:01:31.027
'Morning. Um--

23
00:01:31.047 --> 00:01:32.309
- Oh. good.
- Sully?

24
00:01:32.329 --> 00:01:33.510
Listen. I'm glad you're here.

25
00:01:33.530 --> 00:01:34.992
I need to go to New York
with Cal.

26
00:01:35.012 --> 00:01:37.755
It looks like his father
isn't doing too well.

27
00:01:37.775 --> 00:01:38.837
- Oh. no.
- Ah.

28
00:01:38.857 --> 00:01:40.959
Is it serious?

29
00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:43.402
Prostate cancer.

30
00:01:43.422 --> 00:01:45.164
Oh. I'm so sorry.

31
00:01:45.184 --> 00:01:47.207
I know I just got back.

32
00:01:47.227 --> 00:01:49.449
but I feel like
I need to be there with him.

33
00:01:49.469 --> 00:01:51.131
You take as much time
as you need.

34
00:01:51.151 --> 00:01:54.135
Thank you.
I'll call when I get there.

35
00:01:58.400 --> 00:02:02.865
Should we have told her
about the new luxury resort?

36
00:02:02.885 --> 00:02:05.469
We don't know exactly
what's going on yet.

37
00:02:05.489 --> 00:02:07.050
You're probably right.

38
00:02:12.657 --> 00:02:15.841
♪ Is this as good
as it's gonna get ♪

39
00:02:15.861 --> 00:02:18.364
♪ I've given all I can give ♪

40
00:02:18.384 --> 00:02:22.409
♪ But the rivers
still get wider. wider ♪

41
00:02:22.429 --> 00:02:26.053
♪ We've been here all along ♪

42
00:02:26.073 --> 00:02:28.136
♪ Through the valleys
we carry on ♪

43
00:02:28.156 --> 00:02:31.620
♪ The journey
takes us higher. higher ♪

44
00:02:31.640 --> 00:02:33.863
♪ This could be your home
if we try to build it ♪

45
00:02:33.883 --> 00:02:36.065
♪ This could be your life
that's one in a million ♪

46
00:02:36.085 --> 00:02:38.548
♪ All the hard times.
yeah. they were worth it ♪

47
00:02:38.568 --> 00:02:41.031
♪ Time and time and time again ♪

48
00:02:42.493 --> 00:02:46.157
♪ Oh. oh-whoa-whoa. hey
whoa-oh-whoa-oh ♪

49
00:02:46.177 --> 00:02:48.040
♪ Oh-whoa-oh-whoa-oh ♪

50
00:02:48.060 --> 00:02:51.043
♪ Time and time
and time again ♪

51
00:02:51.944 --> 00:02:53.046
And you'll let me know

52
00:02:53.066 --> 00:02:54.728
if you hear
anything more about it?

53
00:02:54.748 --> 00:02:55.849
- <i>Sure.</i>
- Great.

54
00:02:55.869 --> 00:02:58.212
- <i>Okay.</i>
- Thanks.

55
00:02:58.232 --> 00:02:59.814
Well?

56
00:02:59.834 --> 00:03:01.336
Nobody seems to know anything

57
00:03:01.356 --> 00:03:03.458
about who's behind
this new development.

58
00:03:06.562 --> 00:03:07.944
You're back.

59
00:03:07.964 --> 00:03:09.786
Yeah.

60
00:03:09.806 --> 00:03:11.067
So?

61
00:03:11.087 --> 00:03:13.430
The realtor said
it was a private sale.

62
00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:15.072
Wasn't even listed.

63
00:03:15.092 --> 00:03:17.475
But did they say who bought it?

64
00:03:17.495 --> 00:03:20.398
- Mm-hmm.
- And?

65
00:03:20.418 --> 00:03:23.522
They said it was the same guy
that owns the golf course

66
00:03:23.542 --> 00:03:25.324
on the other side of the lake.

67
00:03:25.344 --> 00:03:27.647
You've got to be kidding me.
Glenn?

68
00:03:27.667 --> 00:03:29.409
Looks that way.

69
00:03:29.429 --> 00:03:31.892
I can't believe this.

70
00:03:31.912 --> 00:03:35.176
That guy is a bad rash.
Come on. Frank.

71
00:03:35.196 --> 00:03:37.018
Uh. where are you going?

72
00:03:37.038 --> 00:03:38.660
I'm going to go see Glenn.

73
00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:40.783
Are you sure that's a good idea?

74
00:03:40.803 --> 00:03:43.066
Somebody's got to do something.
You with me. Frank?

75
00:03:43.086 --> 00:03:45.188
Right behind you. Sully.

76
00:03:47.131 --> 00:03:49.954
You really want to do this.
Frank?

77
00:04:16.366 --> 00:04:17.707
I don't understand.

78
00:04:17.727 --> 00:04:20.350
- Why do you have to move to the farm?
- I told you. Sedona.

79
00:04:20.370 --> 00:04:22.513
I want to go to a school
with real teachers.

80
00:04:22.533 --> 00:04:24.595
But what about Sierra
and Dakota?

81
00:04:24.615 --> 00:04:25.957
They're going to miss you.

82
00:04:25.977 --> 00:04:28.740
You guys can always
come visit.

83
00:04:30.422 --> 00:04:32.525
Will you ever come back?

84
00:04:33.947 --> 00:04:36.049
I don't know.

85
00:04:44.079 --> 00:04:46.181
I need to go.

86
00:04:49.726 --> 00:04:52.589
I'm going to really miss you.
Cal.

87
00:04:52.609 --> 00:04:54.852
I'm going to miss you. too.

88
00:05:05.665 --> 00:05:09.690
You just couldn't drop it.
could you. Glenn?

89
00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.613
Sully. What a surprise.

90
00:05:12.633 --> 00:05:16.217
I didn't realise you
and your friend were golfers.

91
00:05:16.237 --> 00:05:18.340
We're not.

92
00:05:18.841 --> 00:05:20.302
Yeah. I'm really sorry.

93
00:05:20.322 --> 00:05:22.465
but the greens
are for paying players only.

94
00:05:22.485 --> 00:05:24.147
I saw the sign.

95
00:05:24.167 --> 00:05:26.310
We know that you bought
the land next to the Crossing.

96
00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:28.552
Yeah. It was a great deal.

97
00:05:28.572 --> 00:05:30.194
Is there a problem?

98
00:05:30.214 --> 00:05:33.478
Cut the crap. Glenn.
You did this just to spite me.

99
00:05:33.498 --> 00:05:35.240
Don't flatter yourself. Sully.

100
00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:36.962
Like I told you before.
it's just business.

101
00:05:36.982 --> 00:05:39.165
You couldn't build
somewhere else?

102
00:05:39.185 --> 00:05:42.609
I really don't need
to explain myself to you.

103
00:05:42.629 --> 00:05:47.094
So. if we're done here.
I got a game to get back to.

104
00:05:47.114 --> 00:05:48.977
This is my livelihood
you're messing with. Glenn!

105
00:05:48.997 --> 00:05:49.938
Sully--

106
00:05:49.958 --> 00:05:51.580
Do I need to call security?

107
00:05:51.600 --> 00:05:52.941
He's not worth it.

108
00:05:52.961 --> 00:05:54.704
Don't let him get to you.

109
00:05:54.724 --> 00:05:57.767
Come on. Let's go.

110
00:06:06.297 --> 00:06:08.360
I really appreciate you
driving us to the airport. Syd.

111
00:06:08.380 --> 00:06:10.963
Oh. not a problem.
I'm happy to help.

112
00:06:10.983 --> 00:06:12.565
Well. I know how busy
you probably are

113
00:06:12.585 --> 00:06:14.287
looking at places with Rob.

114
00:06:14.307 --> 00:06:17.451
I still can't believe
his landlord did that to him.

115
00:06:17.471 --> 00:06:22.096
Yeah. It was a bit of a shock.
but we'll figure it out.

116
00:06:23.638 --> 00:06:26.342
So.

117
00:06:26.362 --> 00:06:28.144
you're finally going to meet
Cal's parents. huh?

118
00:06:28.164 --> 00:06:29.706
That's a pretty big step.

119
00:06:29.726 --> 00:06:34.511
Yeah. I just wish it was
under better circumstances.

120
00:06:36.093 --> 00:06:37.715
You know. to be honest.
I'm a little nervous.

121
00:06:37.735 --> 00:06:40.479
Why?

122
00:06:40.499 --> 00:06:42.641
I want them to like me.

123
00:06:42.661 --> 00:06:44.924
They're going to love you.
Maggie.

124
00:06:44.944 --> 00:06:47.727
I hope you're right.

125
00:06:47.747 --> 00:06:50.050
What about you?

126
00:06:50.070 --> 00:06:51.692
Things going any better
with Rafe?

127
00:06:51.712 --> 00:06:55.216
We still haven't really found
the time to be together.

128
00:06:55.236 --> 00:06:56.858
I was supposed to hang out
with him yesterday.

129
00:06:56.878 --> 00:07:00.302
but he got called in
to Search and Rescue.

130
00:07:00.322 --> 00:07:02.825
Oh. yeah. No. I know.
I was there.

131
00:07:02.845 --> 00:07:04.708
Really? He didn't mention it.

132
00:07:04.728 --> 00:07:07.992
Probably 'cause the new chief
wouldn't let me help.

133
00:07:08.012 --> 00:07:09.593
Wait. Why?

134
00:07:09.613 --> 00:07:11.716
Not licensed in Canada.

135
00:07:11.736 --> 00:07:14.119
and he didn't want me to be
a liability.

136
00:07:14.139 --> 00:07:16.241
And that didn't bother you?

137
00:07:17.823 --> 00:07:20.166
No point risking
another lawsuit.

138
00:07:25.312 --> 00:07:27.855
I should finish packing.

139
00:07:34.764 --> 00:07:36.025
'Morning. Edna.

140
00:07:36.045 --> 00:07:38.348
I got a fresh pot of coffee
brewing.

141
00:07:38.368 --> 00:07:41.111
Thank you.

142
00:07:41.131 --> 00:07:43.154
Sully not around?

143
00:07:43.174 --> 00:07:45.316
No. He's out with Frank. Why?

144
00:07:45.336 --> 00:07:48.480
He seemed pretty upset yesterday

145
00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:50.202
after birdwatching.

146
00:07:50.222 --> 00:07:53.206
That sign you saw?

147
00:07:53.226 --> 00:07:56.169
Turns out the development's
owned by a guy named Glenn.

148
00:07:56.189 --> 00:07:59.653
and that's the same guy
who tried to buy the Crossing

149
00:07:59.673 --> 00:08:01.295
out from under us
a couple of months ago.

150
00:08:01.315 --> 00:08:02.977
Really?

151
00:08:02.997 --> 00:08:04.419
I should have known

152
00:08:04.439 --> 00:08:06.982
getting rid of him
wouldn't be that easy.

153
00:08:07.002 --> 00:08:09.185
Ugh.

154
00:08:09.205 --> 00:08:10.947
You okay?

155
00:08:10.967 --> 00:08:13.069
Just a little bit of a headache.

156
00:08:14.531 --> 00:08:17.074
Woke up at 3:00 a.m.
with another hot flash.

157
00:08:17.094 --> 00:08:20.478
You really need to
talk to your doctor.

158
00:08:20.498 --> 00:08:22.681
Okay. I'll make an appointment.

159
00:08:24.223 --> 00:08:26.806
Oh. by the way.
that couple from Cabin 12

160
00:08:26.826 --> 00:08:28.488
checked out this morning.

161
00:08:28.508 --> 00:08:30.250
I'll help you with your bags
when you're ready.

162
00:08:30.270 --> 00:08:31.852
Believe it or not.

163
00:08:31.872 --> 00:08:35.176
that little cabin
is starting to grow on me.

164
00:08:35.196 --> 00:08:37.499
I thought you said it needed
a lot of work.

165
00:08:37.519 --> 00:08:40.863
I think that might be
part of its appeal.

166
00:08:40.883 --> 00:08:43.786
Anyway. better get back to it.

167
00:08:46.650 --> 00:08:47.991
Say hi to Sully for me.

168
00:08:48.011 --> 00:08:50.114
Will do.

169
00:08:53.618 --> 00:08:55.781
"Part of its appeal"?

170
00:09:11.960 --> 00:09:13.742
Ready?

171
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:16.265
Let's just go
before I change my mind.

172
00:09:16.285 --> 00:09:17.687
All right.

173
00:09:22.693 --> 00:09:24.795
Okay.

174
00:09:37.791 --> 00:09:39.894
Where have you been?

175
00:09:40.795 --> 00:09:42.457
I was starting to worry.

176
00:09:42.477 --> 00:09:46.782
Well. got nowhere
with Glenn.

177
00:09:46.802 --> 00:09:49.425
so I went over to City Hall

178
00:09:49.445 --> 00:09:52.269
to see if we can pull
his permits.

179
00:09:52.289 --> 00:09:53.470
And?

180
00:09:53.490 --> 00:09:55.312
It's all filed right.

181
00:09:55.332 --> 00:09:57.795
So. there's nothing we can do
to stop this?

182
00:09:57.815 --> 00:10:00.198
Doesn't look like it.

183
00:10:00.218 --> 00:10:02.681
I'm not sure how we're gonna
compete with a place like that.

184
00:10:02.701 --> 00:10:05.444
Well. we still have time
to think.

185
00:10:05.464 --> 00:10:07.827
They're not going to be open
for a while.

186
00:10:10.190 --> 00:10:12.573
I'm going to take a walk.

187
00:10:12.593 --> 00:10:14.695
Sully?

188
00:10:15.797 --> 00:10:17.459
You want some company?

189
00:10:17.479 --> 00:10:20.182
No. I'm fine. Frank.

190
00:10:41.748 --> 00:10:43.650
210

191
00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:45.212
<i>- Dad?</i>
- Hey. bud.

192
00:10:45.232 --> 00:10:47.735
Thought I'd call and check in.
See how things are going.

193
00:10:47.755 --> 00:10:49.097
<i>I love it here.</i>

194
00:10:49.117 --> 00:10:51.019
I made friends with a kid
named Max.

195
00:10:51.039 --> 00:10:52.541
- Uh-huh?
<i>- He showed me a video</i>

196
00:10:52.561 --> 00:10:54.303
of these robot waiters
they have in Japan.

197
00:10:54.323 --> 00:10:55.985
<i>Maybe you could do something
like that</i>

198
00:10:56.005 --> 00:10:57.247
<i>at your new restaurant.</i>

199
00:10:58.288 --> 00:10:59.750
That's a good idea.

200
00:10:59.770 --> 00:11:01.752
but I think that's a little
outside our price range.

201
00:11:01.772 --> 00:11:04.475
Is the diner going to be
finished when I get back?

202
00:11:04.495 --> 00:11:06.478
Uh. things are taking
a little longer than I thought.

203
00:11:06.498 --> 00:11:09.722
but. yeah. We'll be good.

204
00:11:09.742 --> 00:11:11.323
Hey. how's it going
with you and Gram?

205
00:11:11.343 --> 00:11:12.485
You two get along?

206
00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:15.048
Yeah. She's awesome.

207
00:11:15.068 --> 00:11:16.610
I miss you. bud.

208
00:11:16.630 --> 00:11:17.891
<i>Got to go. Dad.</i>

209
00:11:17.911 --> 00:11:20.855
Finn? Hey.

210
00:11:23.518 --> 00:11:25.620
Right.

211
00:11:28.644 --> 00:11:29.705
Hi. Edna.

212
00:11:29.725 --> 00:11:32.749
Hey.

213
00:11:32.769 --> 00:11:36.394
Just thought I'd stop by.
See how things are going.

214
00:11:36.414 --> 00:11:38.076
Perfect timing.

215
00:11:38.096 --> 00:11:39.557
Here. Try one of these for me.

216
00:11:39.577 --> 00:11:42.401
- Tell me what you think.
- All right.

217
00:11:44.383 --> 00:11:46.846
Mmm.

218
00:11:46.866 --> 00:11:48.968
That's delicious.

219
00:11:49.589 --> 00:11:51.852
Those are a lot of brownies.

220
00:11:53.554 --> 00:11:54.896
This have anything to do with

221
00:11:54.916 --> 00:11:57.299
that new development
Sully was telling me about?

222
00:11:57.319 --> 00:12:01.143
Yeah.
Trying to keep my mind off it.

223
00:12:01.163 --> 00:12:02.625
But I can't believe

224
00:12:02.645 --> 00:12:04.988
that Glenn would do something
like this.

225
00:12:05.008 --> 00:12:06.750
Glenn's behind this?

226
00:12:06.770 --> 00:12:08.192
Yeah. We found out this morning.

227
00:12:08.212 --> 00:12:09.713
So. what do we do now?

228
00:12:09.733 --> 00:12:11.796
I don't think there's anything
we can do.

229
00:12:11.816 --> 00:12:13.718
Business as usual.
at least for now.

230
00:12:13.738 --> 00:12:15.921
And where's Sully?

231
00:12:15.941 --> 00:12:18.604
He went for a walk.
Needed to clear his head.

232
00:12:18.624 --> 00:12:21.247
Can you get me a baking soda
from the back?

233
00:12:21.267 --> 00:12:24.010
- Sure.
- Merci.

234
00:12:27.595 --> 00:12:30.418
Ah. Jacob! Tansi. Hello.

235
00:12:30.438 --> 00:12:32.100
Hi. Edna.

236
00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:33.782
How'd it go at the university?

237
00:12:33.802 --> 00:12:36.706
I can't believe how big
their mycology department is.

238
00:12:36.726 --> 00:12:39.509
Twice the size
of the one we have back home.

239
00:12:39.529 --> 00:12:40.591
Are they treating you good?

240
00:12:40.611 --> 00:12:41.872
Oh. yeah.

241
00:12:41.892 --> 00:12:43.754
Everyone's being really nice
to me.

242
00:12:43.774 --> 00:12:45.116
Good. Are you hungry?

243
00:12:45.136 --> 00:12:46.598
I made some fresh brownies.

244
00:12:46.618 --> 00:12:49.601
Thanks. but I try not to eat
too much sugar.

245
00:12:49.621 --> 00:12:51.444
Well. I can make you
something else.

246
00:12:51.464 --> 00:12:53.566
I'm good. Auntie. Thanks.

247
00:12:58.792 --> 00:13:02.216
Well. hello again.

248
00:13:02.236 --> 00:13:04.579
Hey.

249
00:13:08.244 --> 00:13:11.668
Uh. Lola? You don't have to
worry about that.

250
00:13:11.688 --> 00:13:13.750
I tidied that up this morning.

251
00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:16.554
Oh.

252
00:13:16.574 --> 00:13:18.716
But if do you want to help me.

253
00:13:18.736 --> 00:13:20.318
you two can start unpacking

254
00:13:20.338 --> 00:13:23.041
that new shipment of T-shirts
in the back.

255
00:13:23.061 --> 00:13:24.563
I'd be happy to.

256
00:13:24.583 --> 00:13:25.685
Oh. that's okay.

257
00:13:25.705 --> 00:13:27.006
I can do it myself.

258
00:13:27.026 --> 00:13:29.689
I'm sure you've got other things
you can do.

259
00:13:29.709 --> 00:13:32.132
Not really.
I'm done for the day.

260
00:13:32.152 --> 00:13:34.655
so I'm all yours.

261
00:13:34.675 --> 00:13:36.778
Okay.

262
00:13:42.765 --> 00:13:44.427
Listen. About the other night--

263
00:13:44.447 --> 00:13:46.109
Don't worry about it.

264
00:13:46.129 --> 00:13:48.232
It could have happened
to anyone.

265
00:13:48.692 --> 00:13:50.675
I know.
but I feel really bad about it.

266
00:13:50.695 --> 00:13:53.158
and I ruined your shirt.

267
00:13:53.178 --> 00:13:55.080
So. can you please
just let me buy you a new one

268
00:13:55.100 --> 00:13:56.281
so I can make it up to you?

269
00:13:56.301 --> 00:13:58.083
It's just a shirt.

270
00:13:58.103 --> 00:13:59.886
It's really okay.

271
00:13:59.906 --> 00:14:02.529
But. uh. I haven't had a chance

272
00:14:02.549 --> 00:14:05.012
to do any sightseeing
around Nova Scotia yet.

273
00:14:07.034 --> 00:14:09.097
Oh.

274
00:14:09.117 --> 00:14:11.900
Here you go.

275
00:14:11.920 --> 00:14:12.941
What's this?

276
00:14:12.961 --> 00:14:14.623
A visitor's map.

277
00:14:14.643 --> 00:14:18.228
I was kind of thinking
you could show me around.

278
00:14:19.569 --> 00:14:20.991
Oh.

279
00:14:21.011 --> 00:14:23.674
You did say you wanted to
make it up to me. right?

280
00:14:25.096 --> 00:14:26.157
Right.

281
00:14:26.177 --> 00:14:27.759
Great.

282
00:14:27.779 --> 00:14:29.802
Let's finish folding
this box of T-shirts

283
00:14:29.822 --> 00:14:31.924
and head out.

284
00:14:47.403 --> 00:14:49.505
I've never been to Woodstock
before.

285
00:14:51.047 --> 00:14:52.749
Doesn't look anything
like I thought it would.

286
00:14:52.769 --> 00:14:55.152
What were you expecting.
beatniks and hippies?

287
00:14:55.172 --> 00:14:57.975
Yeah. actually.

288
00:14:59.657 --> 00:15:02.681
Hasn't been that way around here
in a long time.

289
00:15:05.224 --> 00:15:06.405
So. how come your parents

290
00:15:06.425 --> 00:15:09.009
don't live in
the old school bus anymore?

291
00:15:09.029 --> 00:15:11.452
Well. my mom convinced my dad

292
00:15:11.472 --> 00:15:12.733
to move to
my grandparents' farm

293
00:15:12.753 --> 00:15:14.015
after my grandfather died.

294
00:15:14.035 --> 00:15:15.777
So. they're farmers now?

295
00:15:15.797 --> 00:15:17.579
No. They just live there.

296
00:15:17.599 --> 00:15:20.222
They lease the land
to local farmers.

297
00:15:22.965 --> 00:15:25.308
When was the last time
you saw them?

298
00:15:27.090 --> 00:15:30.314
Not since Lynne passed away.

299
00:15:31.576 --> 00:15:33.518
Why not?

300
00:15:33.538 --> 00:15:35.440
I was never that close
with my father.

301
00:15:35.460 --> 00:15:37.563
He was too unpredictable.

302
00:15:39.465 --> 00:15:42.008
To be honest. I just hope
he doesn't answer the door

303
00:15:42.028 --> 00:15:43.890
wearing a tinfoil hat.

304
00:15:43.910 --> 00:15:46.614
Well. even if he does.

305
00:15:46.634 --> 00:15:48.616
you don't have anything
to be embarrassed about.

306
00:15:48.636 --> 00:15:50.738
I'll be fine.

307
00:15:52.641 --> 00:15:55.664
Well. can't say
I didn't warn you.

308
00:16:02.493 --> 00:16:04.075
Great minds think alike.

309
00:16:04.095 --> 00:16:08.800
Thought you'd be writing
the great Canadian novel.

310
00:16:10.502 --> 00:16:12.124
Writer's block.

311
00:16:12.144 --> 00:16:14.247
I needed a break.

312
00:16:16.229 --> 00:16:17.451
How are you doing?

313
00:16:17.471 --> 00:16:20.534
Edna told me all about

314
00:16:20.554 --> 00:16:22.657
what's going on with Glenn.

315
00:16:24.639 --> 00:16:27.543
Yeah. He's a problem.

316
00:16:27.563 --> 00:16:29.705
I don't know
how his development's

317
00:16:29.725 --> 00:16:31.908
going to affect the business.

318
00:16:31.928 --> 00:16:34.351
Any idea
of what you might do?

319
00:16:34.371 --> 00:16:36.674
No clue.

320
00:16:36.694 --> 00:16:38.956
Well. looks like we're both
kind of stuck. then.

321
00:16:38.976 --> 00:16:41.399
I guess so.

322
00:16:41.419 --> 00:16:44.043
You want to get out of here?

323
00:16:44.063 --> 00:16:45.845
You feel like
a change of scenery?

324
00:16:45.865 --> 00:16:47.927
You know.

325
00:16:47.947 --> 00:16:51.972
I was thinking of heading over
to the Halifax boardwalk.

326
00:16:51.992 --> 00:16:54.135
if you feel like joining me.

327
00:16:55.797 --> 00:16:57.659
You know what?

328
00:16:57.679 --> 00:16:58.720
Why not?

329
00:17:32.521 --> 00:17:34.503
Hey.

330
00:17:34.523 --> 00:17:37.747
It's going to be okay.

331
00:17:37.767 --> 00:17:40.430
Just try to remember to breathe. okay?

332
00:17:41.852 --> 00:17:43.954
Let's go.

333
00:17:46.497 --> 00:17:48.600
Marissa. they're here!

334
00:17:48.620 --> 00:17:50.522
Glad you made it.

335
00:17:50.542 --> 00:17:52.164
Welcome home. son.

336
00:17:52.184 --> 00:17:54.647
Hi. Dad.

337
00:17:54.667 --> 00:17:57.050
And this must be Maggie.

338
00:17:57.070 --> 00:17:59.013
Sedona's told us so much
about you.

339
00:17:59.033 --> 00:18:01.215
Ah. Nice to meet you. Mr. Jones.

340
00:18:01.235 --> 00:18:02.897
It's Jed. Please.

341
00:18:02.917 --> 00:18:04.579
It's nice to meet you.

342
00:18:04.599 --> 00:18:08.023
Jed?
The doctor said take it easy.

343
00:18:08.043 --> 00:18:09.345
California!

344
00:18:09.365 --> 00:18:13.310
Oh. I can't believe
you're finally here.

345
00:18:13.330 --> 00:18:16.514
Hey. Mom.

346
00:18:16.534 --> 00:18:18.436
I was so excited
to hear you were coming.

347
00:18:18.456 --> 00:18:20.238
Please come in.

348
00:18:20.258 --> 00:18:21.880
I was just getting
some tea and cake ready.

349
00:18:21.900 --> 00:18:24.002
- Come.
- Come on in.

350
00:18:24.503 --> 00:18:27.046
- After you.
- Thank you.

351
00:18:28.308 --> 00:18:30.410
It's beautiful.

352
00:18:52.537 --> 00:18:55.961
So. Edna said that you're here
to do some research?

353
00:18:55.981 --> 00:18:57.042
Yeah.

354
00:18:57.062 --> 00:18:58.604
I'm doing my thesis on lichen.

355
00:18:58.624 --> 00:19:00.006
What's that?

356
00:19:00.026 --> 00:19:01.928
It's made up of two organisms

357
00:19:01.948 --> 00:19:03.970
that live together
symbiotically.

358
00:19:03.990 --> 00:19:05.893
An algae and a fungus.

359
00:19:05.913 --> 00:19:08.856
I find it fascinating because
it doesn't have any roots.

360
00:19:08.876 --> 00:19:12.220
It just pulls its nutrients
directly from the air.

361
00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:13.782
and I'm exploring
how it might be used

362
00:19:13.802 --> 00:19:14.864
as a natural air filter

363
00:19:14.884 --> 00:19:17.426
to help the environment.

364
00:19:21.011 --> 00:19:24.195
Sorry.
I can get a little carried away.

365
00:19:24.215 --> 00:19:27.238
I forget not everyone's
as interested in this as I am.

366
00:19:27.258 --> 00:19:29.241
I think it's really nice
to hear someone

367
00:19:29.261 --> 00:19:31.844
so passionate about their work.

368
00:19:34.747 --> 00:19:37.971
Well. what about you?
What do you do?

369
00:19:37.991 --> 00:19:41.736
I'm doing my internship
for my social work degree.

370
00:19:41.756 --> 00:19:43.618
I want to help troubled teens.

371
00:19:43.638 --> 00:19:45.460
So. I guess we're both trying

372
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:46.762
to make a difference
in the world.

373
00:19:47.923 --> 00:19:50.106
Yeah. I guess so.

374
00:19:57.415 --> 00:19:59.117
You want to take a ride
on the Bluenose with me?

375
00:19:59.137 --> 00:20:00.238
Sure.

376
00:20:00.258 --> 00:20:02.360
Yeah? All right.

377
00:20:06.746 --> 00:20:08.448
That was delicious.

378
00:20:08.468 --> 00:20:11.211
My peach cake
was always Cal's favourite.

379
00:20:11.231 --> 00:20:13.774
Marissa is a great baker.

380
00:20:13.794 --> 00:20:16.137
We took one of her cherry pies

381
00:20:16.157 --> 00:20:17.899
to the neighbours'
for game night.

382
00:20:17.919 --> 00:20:19.661
and they couldn't stop talking
about it.

383
00:20:19.681 --> 00:20:22.385
Game night?

384
00:20:22.405 --> 00:20:25.028
Well. it was your mother's idea.

385
00:20:25.048 --> 00:20:27.431
It's good to get your father
out of the house

386
00:20:27.451 --> 00:20:28.832
every once in a while.

387
00:20:28.852 --> 00:20:29.954
You look great. California.

388
00:20:29.974 --> 00:20:31.555
I can see the fresh air
agrees with you.

389
00:20:31.575 --> 00:20:33.558
Uh. thanks.

390
00:20:33.578 --> 00:20:37.042
I like "Cal." Remember. Dad?

391
00:20:37.062 --> 00:20:39.765
I don't really--
I still don't understand

392
00:20:39.785 --> 00:20:42.729
why you'd want to change
a perfectly good name.

393
00:20:42.749 --> 00:20:45.132
Uh. so Cal was named

394
00:20:45.152 --> 00:20:48.135
on one of our road trips
to California.

395
00:20:48.155 --> 00:20:50.338
Marissa. she went into labour.

396
00:20:50.358 --> 00:20:53.382
We couldn't make it
to the hospital in time.

397
00:20:53.402 --> 00:20:55.404
She had to have him right there
on the side of the road.

398
00:20:55.424 --> 00:20:56.626
I will never forget that day.

399
00:20:56.646 --> 00:20:58.748
Yeah.

400
00:20:59.289 --> 00:21:01.311
So. how is Sedona doing?

401
00:21:01.331 --> 00:21:03.874
Very well. thanks to you.

402
00:21:03.894 --> 00:21:06.117
We were hoping she could come.

403
00:21:06.137 --> 00:21:07.318
but her husband's out of town.

404
00:21:07.338 --> 00:21:09.601
She couldn't find any help
for the kids.

405
00:21:09.621 --> 00:21:11.483
So. maybe next time.

406
00:21:11.503 --> 00:21:14.647
Sedona tells us
that you're a neurosurgeon.

407
00:21:14.667 --> 00:21:18.452
Yeah. I'm helping my father
run his campground now. though.

408
00:21:18.472 --> 00:21:20.334
It's a little less hectic.

409
00:21:20.354 --> 00:21:22.537
and needed a change of pace.

410
00:21:22.557 --> 00:21:24.499
Well. makes sense.

411
00:21:24.519 --> 00:21:27.262
I mean. who needs
all that stress in their life?

412
00:21:27.282 --> 00:21:28.464
That was one of the reasons

413
00:21:28.484 --> 00:21:32.268
that I was against Cal
going to law school.

414
00:21:32.288 --> 00:21:34.751
but he wouldn't listen to me.

415
00:21:34.771 --> 00:21:37.795
Anyway. I'm just glad that

416
00:21:37.815 --> 00:21:40.398
he finally came to his senses.

417
00:21:40.418 --> 00:21:42.801
Can we talk about
something else?

418
00:21:42.821 --> 00:21:44.963
Please?

419
00:21:47.346 --> 00:21:50.010
Will Sierra and Dakota join us?

420
00:21:50.030 --> 00:21:54.014
Oh. Unfortunately.
they couldn't make it.

421
00:21:54.034 --> 00:21:56.938
See. Cal's brother.
he's in the army.

422
00:21:56.958 --> 00:21:58.420
and his little sister Sierra.

423
00:21:58.440 --> 00:22:00.943
she is a chip off the old block.

424
00:22:00.963 --> 00:22:03.306
She loves to travel.

425
00:22:03.326 --> 00:22:05.949
She's just always on
some sort of adventure.

426
00:22:05.969 --> 00:22:07.671
Maggie.
can I get you another slice?

427
00:22:07.691 --> 00:22:09.914
No. I'm good. thank you.

428
00:22:09.934 --> 00:22:12.236
Jed. you haven't touched yours.

429
00:22:12.256 --> 00:22:13.758
Oh. I'm not hungry.

430
00:22:13.778 --> 00:22:16.602
Well. remember the doctor said
you have to keep your weight on.

431
00:22:16.622 --> 00:22:19.405
You know your mother.
Just worries too much about me.

432
00:22:19.425 --> 00:22:22.809
Well. what are the doctors
saying. anyway?

433
00:22:25.192 --> 00:22:26.574
We don't need to talk about

434
00:22:26.594 --> 00:22:28.135
that kind of stuff right now.
do we?

435
00:22:28.155 --> 00:22:30.698
I mean. Maggie.
she just got here.

436
00:22:30.718 --> 00:22:33.021
I would kind of like
to show her around.

437
00:22:33.041 --> 00:22:34.423
What do you say. Maggie? Yeah?

438
00:22:34.443 --> 00:22:36.826
Uh. yeah. That'd be nice.

439
00:22:36.846 --> 00:22:38.428
That's great.

440
00:22:38.448 --> 00:22:40.831
Okay.

441
00:22:40.851 --> 00:22:43.113
No. no. Leave those. please.
Cal and I will finish up.

442
00:22:43.133 --> 00:22:44.515
Okay. You sure I can't help?

443
00:22:44.535 --> 00:22:46.277
It's good. Go ahead.

444
00:22:46.297 --> 00:22:48.440
Come on. Follow me.

445
00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:51.243
Let's take a little walk.

446
00:22:51.263 --> 00:22:52.985
I want to show you
one of Cal's favourite places.

447
00:23:02.877 --> 00:23:05.100
You were right. This is nice.

448
00:23:07.002 --> 00:23:09.265
Haven't been down here
in a while.

449
00:23:09.285 --> 00:23:10.586
Why not?

450
00:23:10.606 --> 00:23:12.348
I just always thought

451
00:23:12.368 --> 00:23:15.072
it was a place for couples.
you know?

452
00:23:15.092 --> 00:23:17.595
Well. I suppose it is romantic.

453
00:23:17.615 --> 00:23:19.397
Hey. What is that?

454
00:23:19.417 --> 00:23:21.519
Washer toss.

455
00:23:23.021 --> 00:23:24.803
Looks fun.

456
00:23:24.823 --> 00:23:25.885
Show me how to play?

457
00:23:25.905 --> 00:23:28.408
- Okay.
- All right.

458
00:23:31.551 --> 00:23:34.815
All right.
So. you want to throw the washer

459
00:23:34.835 --> 00:23:36.297
into the box.

460
00:23:36.317 --> 00:23:37.699
Three points
if it goes in the pipe.

461
00:23:37.719 --> 00:23:39.541
one point if it goes in the box.

462
00:23:39.561 --> 00:23:42.064
Okay. Seems simple enough.

463
00:23:42.084 --> 00:23:44.988
It's not as easy as it looks.
but give it a try.

464
00:23:45.008 --> 00:23:47.510
Okay.

465
00:23:48.852 --> 00:23:50.474
It's all in the wrist.

466
00:23:50.494 --> 00:23:52.597
Like this.

467
00:23:55.740 --> 00:23:58.003
Ah. So close.

468
00:23:58.023 --> 00:23:59.845
Not bad! Not bad.

469
00:23:59.865 --> 00:24:01.968
All right. How about we make
this a little more interesting?

470
00:24:01.988 --> 00:24:03.209
Huh? What were you thinking?

471
00:24:03.229 --> 00:24:05.492
Five bucks for every one
that goes in the pipe.

472
00:24:05.512 --> 00:24:08.015
Ah.
I don't want to take your money.

473
00:24:08.035 --> 00:24:10.138
Uh. who says
you're going to win?

474
00:24:10.158 --> 00:24:13.101
All right. If you insist.

475
00:24:13.121 --> 00:24:15.264
- All right.
- Be my guest.

476
00:24:19.889 --> 00:24:22.513
- Nice!
- Oh.

477
00:24:22.533 --> 00:24:26.437
Anyway. Cal tells me
that you lease out your land?

478
00:24:26.457 --> 00:24:27.639
Yeah.

479
00:24:27.659 --> 00:24:30.402
The farmers get a place
to grow their crops.

480
00:24:30.422 --> 00:24:32.765
and Marissa and I
don't have to worry about

481
00:24:32.785 --> 00:24:34.006
maintaining the land.

482
00:24:34.026 --> 00:24:35.248
Mm-hmm.

483
00:24:35.268 --> 00:24:36.489
So. yeah. It works for everyone.

484
00:24:36.509 --> 00:24:37.891
What do they grow out here?

485
00:24:37.911 --> 00:24:42.416
Everything from strawberries
to corn. It's all organic.

486
00:24:42.436 --> 00:24:45.220
You won't find any chemicals
or GMOs here. so--

487
00:24:45.240 --> 00:24:48.424
My dad is all about
protecting the land. too.

488
00:24:48.444 --> 00:24:50.226
Yeah.
Sounds like your father and I

489
00:24:50.246 --> 00:24:51.547
are cut from the same cloth.

490
00:24:51.567 --> 00:24:53.189
Yeah. It does.

491
00:24:53.209 --> 00:24:55.352
Anyways.
when I was a little girl.

492
00:24:55.372 --> 00:24:57.074
he used take me to a farm
near our house

493
00:24:57.094 --> 00:24:59.277
and we'd collect eggs.

494
00:24:59.297 --> 00:25:00.718
I used to love feeding
the chickens.

495
00:25:00.738 --> 00:25:02.841
Yeah? Well. here you go.

496
00:25:04.863 --> 00:25:06.726
Cal used to love it here
as a teenager.

497
00:25:06.746 --> 00:25:09.990
He told me. Thank you.

498
00:25:11.551 --> 00:25:13.814
What else did he say
about his childhood?

499
00:25:13.834 --> 00:25:15.937
Uh...

500
00:25:16.477 --> 00:25:18.900
...just that
it was unconventional

501
00:25:18.920 --> 00:25:21.984
and he used to live in
a converted school bus.

502
00:25:22.004 --> 00:25:24.106
Yeah.

503
00:25:25.368 --> 00:25:27.270
Those were happy times.

504
00:25:27.290 --> 00:25:28.712
I miss them.

505
00:25:28.732 --> 00:25:31.836
Marissa and I. we thought
it was important for the kids

506
00:25:31.856 --> 00:25:33.918
to experience life first-hand.

507
00:25:33.938 --> 00:25:35.881
Didn't want them

508
00:25:35.901 --> 00:25:38.003
to just read about it in books.

509
00:25:38.944 --> 00:25:41.007
I look around the world today.

510
00:25:41.027 --> 00:25:43.370
and all those people
with their face

511
00:25:43.390 --> 00:25:46.413
just buried in a screen.

512
00:25:46.433 --> 00:25:48.856
Hardly spend any time outdoors
anymore.

513
00:25:50.839 --> 00:25:52.861
That was what I missed most

514
00:25:52.881 --> 00:25:55.504
when I moved to Boston.

515
00:25:55.524 --> 00:25:57.386
That connection with. you know. nature.

516
00:25:57.406 --> 00:25:58.588
Yeah.

517
00:25:58.608 --> 00:25:59.829
That was one of the reasons

518
00:25:59.849 --> 00:26:02.432
that I went back home
to Nova Scotia.

519
00:26:02.452 --> 00:26:04.955
I can see why Cal
likes you so much.

520
00:26:04.975 --> 00:26:07.318
I like him a lot. too.

521
00:26:07.338 --> 00:26:09.441
Yeah.

522
00:26:11.143 --> 00:26:14.887
Looks like. uh.
the balloon festival's in town.

523
00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:16.129
Ah.

524
00:26:16.149 --> 00:26:17.491
Have you ever been?

525
00:26:17.511 --> 00:26:20.374
Once. a long time ago.

526
00:26:20.394 --> 00:26:22.977
It was incredible.

527
00:26:22.997 --> 00:26:27.182
I took Marissa a few years back.

528
00:26:27.202 --> 00:26:31.427
I think that was the last real
adventure we had together...

529
00:26:33.009 --> 00:26:35.112
...before my diagnosis.

530
00:26:43.301 --> 00:26:45.164
Dad seems to be doing well.

531
00:26:45.184 --> 00:26:50.049
Well. knowing you were coming
really helped lift his spirits.

532
00:26:51.311 --> 00:26:53.534
Game night with the neighbours?

533
00:26:53.554 --> 00:26:55.656
Since when is he okay with that?

534
00:26:56.918 --> 00:27:00.943
Oh. Well. since he started
taking his antipsychotics.

535
00:27:00.963 --> 00:27:03.105
He finally agreed
to get on the meds?

536
00:27:03.125 --> 00:27:05.028
Mm-hmm.

537
00:27:05.048 --> 00:27:06.910
How'd you get him to do that?

538
00:27:06.930 --> 00:27:09.513
I threatened to leave him.

539
00:27:09.533 --> 00:27:10.995
It was the only way
to convince him

540
00:27:11.015 --> 00:27:13.558
to go for treatment.

541
00:27:13.578 --> 00:27:15.680
Mom...

542
00:27:16.501 --> 00:27:19.004
...I don't understand.

543
00:27:19.024 --> 00:27:20.967
Why would he change his mind
now.

544
00:27:20.987 --> 00:27:22.729
after all these years?

545
00:27:22.749 --> 00:27:24.171
I don't want to talk about this.
Cal.

546
00:27:24.191 --> 00:27:27.374
I was hoping for
a really nice visit.

547
00:27:27.394 --> 00:27:29.497
I'm going to go make up
the guest room.

548
00:27:30.038 --> 00:27:32.140
Mom?

549
00:27:34.042 --> 00:27:37.266
- Not again!
- Ha-ha-ha.

550
00:27:37.286 --> 00:27:39.389
All right. Let's see. One. two--

551
00:27:41.491 --> 00:27:43.434
That'll be $25. Mr. Sullivan.

552
00:27:43.454 --> 00:27:45.636
You sure you haven't played
this game before?

553
00:27:45.656 --> 00:27:48.760
Nope. Must be beginner's luck.

554
00:27:48.780 --> 00:27:49.881
Yeah? I feel like

555
00:27:49.901 --> 00:27:51.203
I'm getting hustled.

556
00:27:51.223 --> 00:27:53.285
Okay. Maybe I have played
once or twice.

557
00:27:53.305 --> 00:27:55.368
Ah. I knew it.

558
00:27:55.388 --> 00:27:56.930
Well. it seems like
you're feeling better.

559
00:27:56.950 --> 00:27:59.132
I am. I am. yeah.

560
00:27:59.152 --> 00:28:01.215
So. thanks for taking my mind
off things.

561
00:28:01.235 --> 00:28:03.337
My pleasure.

562
00:28:05.680 --> 00:28:09.585
How about I buy us
some ice cream with my winnings?

563
00:28:09.605 --> 00:28:11.888
I'd love that.

564
00:28:23.942 --> 00:28:27.046
I know being here
isn't easy for you. Cal.

565
00:28:30.951 --> 00:28:35.516
What did Sierra and Dakota
really say when you called them?

566
00:28:38.119 --> 00:28:40.142
I couldn't reach Sierra.

567
00:28:40.162 --> 00:28:43.466
and your brother wouldn't come.

568
00:28:46.049 --> 00:28:47.170
Can you blame him?

569
00:28:48.732 --> 00:28:52.036
And why won't Dad talk to me
about what's going on?

570
00:28:53.818 --> 00:28:56.962
You know how he feels
about discussing his health.

571
00:28:56.982 --> 00:28:59.245
Maggie's a doctor.
Maybe she could help.

572
00:28:59.265 --> 00:29:01.808
I know. but it's difficult
for your father.

573
00:29:01.828 --> 00:29:04.571
He's a private person.
He always has been.

574
00:29:04.591 --> 00:29:06.974
Okay. So. I ask you.

575
00:29:06.994 --> 00:29:08.215
What's going on?

576
00:29:08.235 --> 00:29:09.737
I. uh. hope I'm not

577
00:29:09.757 --> 00:29:11.299
interrupting anything.

578
00:29:11.319 --> 00:29:13.502
Cal and I are just catching up.

579
00:29:13.522 --> 00:29:14.863
Hey. I'm glad you're back.

580
00:29:14.883 --> 00:29:16.746
It's almost time for your pills.

581
00:29:16.766 --> 00:29:20.350
Uh. if it's okay. I think
I'm going to lay down a bit.

582
00:29:20.370 --> 00:29:22.472
Yeah. I'll come with you.

583
00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:30.522
How was the tour?

584
00:29:30.542 --> 00:29:32.645
It was nice.

585
00:29:33.866 --> 00:29:37.851
It's funny. He actually
reminds me a lot of Sully.

586
00:29:39.273 --> 00:29:42.897
My father is nothing
like Sully.

587
00:29:42.917 --> 00:29:45.380
You wouldn't understand.

588
00:29:46.681 --> 00:29:48.784
I don't think I can do this.

589
00:30:01.379 --> 00:30:03.482
624
Lola was looking for you.

590
00:30:04.142 --> 00:30:06.445
Where is she now?

591
00:30:06.465 --> 00:30:07.807
Showing Jacob around Lunenburg.

592
00:30:07.827 --> 00:30:09.929
Oh.

593
00:30:11.271 --> 00:30:13.734
You were gone a while.

594
00:30:13.754 --> 00:30:15.977
Yeah. I took Helen to Halifax.

595
00:30:15.997 --> 00:30:17.699
Really?

596
00:30:17.719 --> 00:30:22.545
Yeah. I needed a distraction
from this Glenn thing.

597
00:30:22.565 --> 00:30:25.428
And did she help distract you?

598
00:30:25.448 --> 00:30:27.110
She asked me to take her.

599
00:30:27.130 --> 00:30:29.593
What was I supposed to do?
Say no?

600
00:30:32.096 --> 00:30:33.838
If you're done.

601
00:30:33.858 --> 00:30:35.360
I'm going to head home
and make some dinner.

602
00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:37.683
Mm-hmm.

603
00:30:37.703 --> 00:30:39.805
See you tomorrow.

604
00:30:49.997 --> 00:30:52.300
I knew this trip was a bad idea.

605
00:30:52.320 --> 00:30:54.062
Being here. you know?

606
00:30:54.082 --> 00:30:56.465
It just opens it all back up.
It's like I never left.

607
00:30:56.485 --> 00:30:58.307
I know. but

608
00:30:58.327 --> 00:31:00.430
I'd give it some time.

609
00:31:04.134 --> 00:31:06.998
All right. You're right.
You're right. I'm sorry.

610
00:31:07.018 --> 00:31:09.241
I shouldn't have snapped.
I just--

611
00:31:09.261 --> 00:31:13.085
Being around my dad
puts me on edge. you know?

612
00:31:13.105 --> 00:31:15.328
I know how hard coming home
can be.

613
00:31:15.348 --> 00:31:16.970
Knock-knock.

614
00:31:16.990 --> 00:31:20.134
I got your father settled.

615
00:31:20.154 --> 00:31:21.455
Um. is there anything you need?

616
00:31:21.475 --> 00:31:24.178
We're good. Thanks. Mom.

617
00:31:24.198 --> 00:31:26.221
I thought I would make us all
a nice dinner tonight.

618
00:31:26.241 --> 00:31:27.663
Um. Maggie.

619
00:31:27.683 --> 00:31:29.825
maybe if you want to join me
in the kitchen?

620
00:31:29.845 --> 00:31:31.347
Keep me company
while I get it started?

621
00:31:31.367 --> 00:31:33.469
I'd be happy to.

622
00:31:35.132 --> 00:31:36.113
You coming?

623
00:31:36.133 --> 00:31:38.876
I'll be down in a little bit.

624
00:31:38.896 --> 00:31:40.998
Okay.

625
00:31:49.108 --> 00:31:51.291
I saved the best for last.

626
00:31:51.311 --> 00:31:53.293
You're really going to
fall in love with this place

627
00:31:53.313 --> 00:31:55.816
when you see it.

628
00:31:58.840 --> 00:32:00.662
Thank you.

629
00:32:00.682 --> 00:32:02.945
Thanks.

630
00:32:02.965 --> 00:32:03.946
Oh.

631
00:32:03.966 --> 00:32:05.748
You need to try and picture

632
00:32:05.768 --> 00:32:07.871
what it's going to look like
renovated.

633
00:32:07.891 --> 00:32:09.593
There's a large area for dining

634
00:32:09.613 --> 00:32:11.715
and a functional kitchen
in the back.

635
00:32:13.177 --> 00:32:14.879
Is that a leak?

636
00:32:14.899 --> 00:32:18.023
Nothing a good contractor
can't fix.

637
00:32:19.985 --> 00:32:22.088
How much was the rent again?

638
00:32:22.869 --> 00:32:26.453
Everything but the utilities
are included.

639
00:32:26.473 --> 00:32:27.695
It's way above my price range.

640
00:32:27.715 --> 00:32:30.538
Listen. I have a couple
other places opening up

641
00:32:30.558 --> 00:32:32.060
in the next few months.

642
00:32:32.080 --> 00:32:34.343
but they're all going to be
around the same price.

643
00:32:34.363 --> 00:32:37.466
Mm-hmm.

644
00:32:37.486 --> 00:32:40.070
Um. yeah. Thanks.
I appreciate your time.

645
00:32:40.090 --> 00:32:42.472
but I don't think
this is going to work out.

646
00:32:42.492 --> 00:32:44.595
Rob. where are you going?

647
00:32:46.257 --> 00:32:47.518
Sorry. He's--

648
00:32:47.538 --> 00:32:49.841
Rob?

649
00:32:59.032 --> 00:33:00.654
Thanks for today.

650
00:33:00.674 --> 00:33:02.777
I had a lot of fun.

651
00:33:03.357 --> 00:33:05.700
Me. too.

652
00:33:07.963 --> 00:33:11.827
Do you think I could get
your number?

653
00:33:13.850 --> 00:33:16.713
Yeah. I guess so.

654
00:33:33.434 --> 00:33:35.977
So. I'll call you later?

655
00:33:35.997 --> 00:33:37.378
Okay.

656
00:33:37.398 --> 00:33:39.501
Thanks again.

657
00:33:45.007 --> 00:33:47.591
You have fun in Lunenburg?

658
00:33:47.611 --> 00:33:49.553
Yeah. I did.

659
00:33:49.573 --> 00:33:52.276
Jacob's
a pretty interesting guy.

660
00:33:52.296 --> 00:33:54.519
I was hoping you'd hit it off.

661
00:33:54.539 --> 00:33:56.641
Is Sully around?

662
00:33:56.661 --> 00:33:58.764
No. He's gone home.

663
00:33:58.784 --> 00:34:01.127
and it's a good thing
you didn't wait around for him.

664
00:34:01.147 --> 00:34:03.089
Turns out he went to Halifax
with Helen.

665
00:34:03.109 --> 00:34:04.611
Who's Helen?

666
00:34:04.631 --> 00:34:06.493
She's that guest
I told you about.

667
00:34:06.513 --> 00:34:08.776
the one he took birdwatching.

668
00:34:08.796 --> 00:34:11.379
Seems like you're not the only
one to make a new friend.

669
00:34:26.417 --> 00:34:28.800
Ma.

670
00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:32.044
how about you let me
do the dishes?

671
00:34:32.064 --> 00:34:33.566
Hey. Why don't you go sit
on the front porch

672
00:34:33.586 --> 00:34:34.687
with your father instead?

673
00:34:34.707 --> 00:34:37.210
Uh--

674
00:34:37.230 --> 00:34:38.852
Oh. he was really
looking forward to

675
00:34:38.872 --> 00:34:41.375
spending some time with you.
Cal.

676
00:34:41.395 --> 00:34:43.497
Okay.

677
00:34:48.323 --> 00:34:50.987
Everything was delicious.
Thank you.

678
00:34:51.007 --> 00:34:53.429
Love to cook.

679
00:34:53.449 --> 00:34:55.272
But I didn't get to do
a whole lot of it

680
00:34:55.292 --> 00:34:56.393
on a camp stove.

681
00:34:56.413 --> 00:34:57.915
Mm-hmm.

682
00:34:57.935 --> 00:35:01.119
Cal seemed pretty quiet
at dinner tonight.

683
00:35:01.139 --> 00:35:04.162
I'm sure he was just tired
from the drive up.

684
00:35:04.182 --> 00:35:06.645
Yeah. I guess so.

685
00:35:06.665 --> 00:35:08.768
I'm going to go finish
clearing the table.

686
00:35:30.414 --> 00:35:33.117
It's nice being together again
like this. isn't it?

687
00:35:35.460 --> 00:35:38.764
Your Maggie. she's a good egg.

688
00:35:38.784 --> 00:35:40.526
Yep.

689
00:35:40.546 --> 00:35:42.248
When I was out
showing her around.

690
00:35:42.268 --> 00:35:45.412
we started talking.

691
00:35:45.432 --> 00:35:48.896
and I got to thinking about
the old school bus

692
00:35:48.916 --> 00:35:51.319
and all those adventures
we used to have.

693
00:35:53.281 --> 00:35:55.544
You still remember them. right?

694
00:35:55.564 --> 00:35:57.586
- Hard to forget.
- Yeah.

695
00:35:57.606 --> 00:36:01.031
I miss those days.

696
00:36:01.051 --> 00:36:04.114
when we were
one big happy family.

697
00:36:04.134 --> 00:36:06.837
Is that what you think?

698
00:36:07.939 --> 00:36:09.961
That we were happy?

699
00:36:09.981 --> 00:36:12.925
Well. I know we had
our ups and downs. Cal.

700
00:36:12.945 --> 00:36:15.047
but what family doesn't?

701
00:36:15.748 --> 00:36:17.530
I think you're downplaying it

702
00:36:17.550 --> 00:36:19.212
a little bit. don't you?

703
00:36:19.232 --> 00:36:20.934
What do you mean?

704
00:36:20.954 --> 00:36:24.739
Why do you think we all left.
Dad?

705
00:36:24.759 --> 00:36:27.022
I don't understand.

706
00:36:27.042 --> 00:36:29.745
Why'd Dakota join the army

707
00:36:29.765 --> 00:36:31.347
as soon as they would take him?

708
00:36:31.367 --> 00:36:33.830
Why is Sierra always travelling?

709
00:36:33.850 --> 00:36:36.513
Why do you think that is?

710
00:36:36.533 --> 00:36:38.756
Because we all wanted to get

711
00:36:38.776 --> 00:36:42.620
as far away from you
as possible.

712
00:36:44.743 --> 00:36:46.205
Cal. that's enough!

713
00:36:46.225 --> 00:36:47.767
It's fine. Marissa.

714
00:36:47.787 --> 00:36:50.210
How can you speak to
your father like that?

715
00:36:50.230 --> 00:36:53.654
Jed... you okay?

716
00:36:53.674 --> 00:36:55.856
Hey.

717
00:36:57.078 --> 00:36:59.180
I'm sorry.

718
00:37:02.965 --> 00:37:05.067
I'm going to talk to him.

719
00:37:15.099 --> 00:37:18.524
Used to love coming in here
to think when I was a kid.

720
00:37:18.544 --> 00:37:19.725
Did you know that
a horse's heart

721
00:37:19.745 --> 00:37:22.048
is five times bigger than ours?

722
00:37:22.068 --> 00:37:24.050
And that
their electromagnetic field

723
00:37:24.070 --> 00:37:25.932
can lower blood pressure

724
00:37:25.952 --> 00:37:27.855
and increase endorphins
in the brain?

725
00:37:27.875 --> 00:37:31.299
I didn't know that.

726
00:37:35.964 --> 00:37:38.908
I can't believe my dad's finally
taking his antipsychotics.

727
00:37:38.928 --> 00:37:41.711
But that's a good thing.
isn't it?

728
00:37:41.731 --> 00:37:43.834
Yeah. it is. It just--

729
00:37:45.736 --> 00:37:47.358
I don't understand
why he didn't do it

730
00:37:47.378 --> 00:37:50.402
when I needed him to. You know?

731
00:37:50.422 --> 00:37:52.564
You don't know
what it was like

732
00:37:52.584 --> 00:37:54.607
growing up with him.

733
00:37:54.627 --> 00:37:57.771
Never knowing
who you were going to get.

734
00:37:57.791 --> 00:37:59.653
Never being able to rely on him.

735
00:37:59.673 --> 00:38:02.016
No. I get it.
I spent years blaming Sully

736
00:38:02.036 --> 00:38:03.738
for never being there
for me. either.

737
00:38:03.758 --> 00:38:06.822
Sully didn't have a choice.

738
00:38:06.842 --> 00:38:09.545
Your mother took you away
from him.

739
00:38:09.565 --> 00:38:12.749
Schizophrenia
isn't a choice. either. Cal.

740
00:38:12.769 --> 00:38:17.875
I know that. Maggie.
but taking his medication was...

741
00:38:19.096 --> 00:38:21.559
...and he didn't.

742
00:38:36.677 --> 00:38:38.540
We're going to figure
this out. Rob.

743
00:38:38.560 --> 00:38:39.941
You just need to stay positive.

744
00:38:39.961 --> 00:38:41.623
Look. We've looked at
every option out there.

745
00:38:41.643 --> 00:38:43.145
There's nothing available.

746
00:38:43.165 --> 00:38:47.550
We're out of options.
I'm out of money.

747
00:38:47.570 --> 00:38:49.192
I need to start making
some decisions. okay?

748
00:38:49.212 --> 00:38:51.395
- What sort of decisions?
- I need to look for a job.

749
00:38:51.415 --> 00:38:53.878
So. you're just going to give up
on finding a place?

750
00:38:53.898 --> 00:38:55.200
We looked.

751
00:38:55.220 --> 00:38:57.042
There's nothing out there.

752
00:38:57.062 --> 00:38:59.044
I can't keep doing this.

753
00:38:59.064 --> 00:39:02.168
Rob!

754
00:39:08.115 --> 00:39:09.176
Sully?

755
00:39:09.196 --> 00:39:10.578
In the kitchen.

756
00:39:10.598 --> 00:39:11.940
Hey.

757
00:39:11.960 --> 00:39:14.062
Good to see you.

758
00:39:16.525 --> 00:39:18.387
I went to the Outpost earlier
to find you.

759
00:39:18.407 --> 00:39:19.469
but you weren't there.

760
00:39:19.489 --> 00:39:20.710
Oh. Sorry I missed you.

761
00:39:20.730 --> 00:39:22.152
I'm making dinner.
You want some?

762
00:39:22.172 --> 00:39:24.395
Yeah. sure. Thanks.

763
00:39:24.415 --> 00:39:26.477
Okay.

764
00:39:26.497 --> 00:39:28.079
So. I heard

765
00:39:28.099 --> 00:39:29.841
you took one of the guests
to Halifax today.

766
00:39:29.861 --> 00:39:32.484
Yeah. Helen Culver.
She's an author.

767
00:39:32.504 --> 00:39:34.407
Came here to finish her book.

768
00:39:34.427 --> 00:39:36.850
Okay.

769
00:39:36.870 --> 00:39:38.051
And is this the same guest

770
00:39:38.071 --> 00:39:40.374
that you took birdwatching
the other day?

771
00:39:40.394 --> 00:39:41.856
What are you getting at?

772
00:39:41.876 --> 00:39:43.738
Nothing.

773
00:39:43.758 --> 00:39:46.781
I think it's nice for you
to have someone to talk to.

774
00:39:46.801 --> 00:39:48.544
She's just a guest.

775
00:39:48.564 --> 00:39:50.666
This hers?

776
00:39:51.607 --> 00:39:53.710
Yeah.

777
00:39:56.293 --> 00:39:58.115
She's pretty.

778
00:39:58.135 --> 00:40:00.958
Yeah? Is that right?
I hadn't really noticed.

779
00:40:03.341 --> 00:40:05.404
You going to sit there.
or you going to give me a hand

780
00:40:05.424 --> 00:40:06.485
setting the table?

781
00:40:06.505 --> 00:40:07.586
Yeah.

782
00:40:31.936 --> 00:40:33.878
Would you mind giving us
a minute?

783
00:40:33.898 --> 00:40:36.000
Of course.

784
00:40:42.588 --> 00:40:44.571
I know things
haven't always been good

785
00:40:44.591 --> 00:40:47.254
between you and your father.

786
00:40:47.274 --> 00:40:50.057
but you didn't have to say
those things to him.

787
00:40:51.038 --> 00:40:52.781
But it's the truth.

788
00:40:52.801 --> 00:40:54.182
He's sick.

789
00:40:54.202 --> 00:40:58.548
I don't want him getting upset.
It's not good for him.

790
00:40:58.568 --> 00:41:02.192
You've been making excuses
for him my entire life.

791
00:41:03.854 --> 00:41:07.238
Why can't you ever see anything
from my perspective?

792
00:41:07.258 --> 00:41:11.323
I don't understand
where all this is coming from.

793
00:41:11.343 --> 00:41:13.005
Cal. Marissa!

794
00:41:13.025 --> 00:41:15.648
I need your help. It's Jed!

795
00:41:21.635 --> 00:41:23.297
840
Maggie?

796
00:41:23.317 --> 00:41:24.619
Oh. my God.

797
00:41:24.639 --> 00:41:26.341
- Jed?
- What happened?

798
00:41:26.361 --> 00:41:28.944
We were just sitting here
talking. and he fainted.

799
00:41:28.964 --> 00:41:31.067
Jed. can you hear me?

800
00:41:31.087 --> 00:41:33.309
I need you to wait a minute
or two before you get up.

801
00:41:33.329 --> 00:41:35.592
I don't want you fainting again.

802
00:41:35.612 --> 00:41:36.833
Do I need to call an ambulance?

803
00:41:36.853 --> 00:41:39.637
No. I'm good. I'm good.
I'm good.

804
00:41:39.657 --> 00:41:41.439
I just got a little light-headed
there for a second.

805
00:41:41.459 --> 00:41:42.961
Are you sure?

806
00:41:42.981 --> 00:41:45.083
Yeah. Yeah.

807
00:41:45.103 --> 00:41:49.208
His pulse is fine.
so I think he'll be okay.

808
00:41:49.228 --> 00:41:50.890
Can you grab him
a glass of water. please?

809
00:41:50.910 --> 00:41:51.932
Yes.

810
00:41:51.952 --> 00:41:53.694
And some pillows
to put under his legs

811
00:41:53.714 --> 00:41:54.935
- to elevate his feet?
- Okay.

812
00:41:54.955 --> 00:41:56.938
This ever happen to you before?

813
00:41:56.958 --> 00:41:59.821
No. no. But I have been
a little dizzy lately.

814
00:41:59.841 --> 00:42:01.263
We should get you something
to eat.

815
00:42:01.283 --> 00:42:02.504
Oh.

816
00:42:02.524 --> 00:42:03.746
You might be
a little hypoglycemic.

817
00:42:03.766 --> 00:42:05.187
- Here you go.
- What's that?

818
00:42:05.207 --> 00:42:06.910
Low blood sugar.

819
00:42:06.930 --> 00:42:08.552
Thank you.

820
00:42:08.572 --> 00:42:10.874
Thanks. Okay.

821
00:42:10.894 --> 00:42:13.157
I told you
you weren't eating enough.

822
00:42:13.177 --> 00:42:14.799
that you should listen to
your doctor

823
00:42:14.819 --> 00:42:16.000
when he told you
to take it easy.

824
00:42:16.020 --> 00:42:18.804
I was excited to see my son.

825
00:42:18.824 --> 00:42:21.167
You feeling better now?

826
00:42:21.187 --> 00:42:22.688
Yeah. A bit.

827
00:42:22.708 --> 00:42:24.451
Is he going to be okay?

828
00:42:24.471 --> 00:42:26.333
Yeah. I think so.

829
00:42:26.353 --> 00:42:28.175
I mean.
I think it would be a good idea

830
00:42:28.195 --> 00:42:29.897
to schedule an appointment
with your doctor

831
00:42:29.917 --> 00:42:32.060
to get a better sense
of what's going on.

832
00:42:32.080 --> 00:42:34.182
You scared me. Jed.

833
00:42:34.202 --> 00:42:35.744
I know.

834
00:42:35.764 --> 00:42:37.586
and I'm sorry.

835
00:42:37.606 --> 00:42:39.268
You have to tell him.

836
00:42:39.288 --> 00:42:41.231
We discussed this.

837
00:42:41.251 --> 00:42:43.433
Tell me what?

838
00:42:43.453 --> 00:42:46.677
Nothing.

839
00:42:46.697 --> 00:42:48.640
He needs to know. Jed.

840
00:42:48.660 --> 00:42:51.243
What are you talking about?

841
00:42:53.666 --> 00:42:55.167
I can't hide it
from him anymore.

842
00:42:55.187 --> 00:42:57.410
He needs to know the truth. Jed.

843
00:42:57.430 --> 00:43:00.734
You promised that
you would let me do this my way.

844
00:43:00.754 --> 00:43:02.376
All right. What's going on?

845
00:43:02.396 --> 00:43:03.618
What aren't you telling me?

846
00:43:03.638 --> 00:43:05.700
- Maybe I should go.
- No.

847
00:43:05.720 --> 00:43:08.463
No. Just stay here. It's fine.

848
00:43:08.483 --> 00:43:10.906
It's okay.

849
00:43:10.926 --> 00:43:13.029
The cancer...

850
00:43:13.730 --> 00:43:16.193
...it's spread to my pancreas.

851
00:43:16.213 --> 00:43:18.716
It's terminal.

852
00:43:20.458 --> 00:43:24.082
♪ One last time... ♪

853
00:43:24.102 --> 00:43:26.205
I'm so sorry. Cal.

854
00:43:27.306 --> 00:43:30.930
♪ This hurt won't heal ♪

855
00:43:30.950 --> 00:43:33.053
♪ All covered up ♪

856
00:43:33.914 --> 00:43:38.299
♪ It's never easy to feel ♪

857
00:43:38.319 --> 00:43:40.502
♪ So fragile. love ♪

858
00:43:40.522 --> 00:43:44.947
♪ When the wind turns cold ♪

859
00:43:44.967 --> 00:43:47.230
♪ The sun hides ♪

860
00:43:47.250 --> 00:43:50.554
♪ Just beyond my soul ♪

